HEADWORD: Rosefinch
<hw>Rose"finch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of numerous species of Asiatic finches of the genera
<gen>Carpodacus</gen>, and <gen>Propasser</gen>, and allied genera, in
which the male is more or less colored with rose red.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

